-- Chinese President Hu Hopes Taiwan Trade Pact Will Start Soon, Xinhua Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-12T23:05:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/chinese-president-hu-hopes-taiwan-trade-pact-will-start-soon-xinhua-says.html

          
          
             Chinese President Hu Jintao said he
hopes the Economic Cooperation Framework Agreement trade pact
with Taiwan will take effect as soon as possible, the official
Xinhua news agency reported yesterday.  
 Economic and trade ties between China and Taiwan have
entered a new stage, Hu said, according to the report.  
